From 74d6735bbb0a5240144ae167d05b13dce08fac30 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Thu, 28 May 2026 21:53:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] replace wallpaperdefault with Oniro wallpaper
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Make the system (home) default wallpaper the same Oniro image already used
for the lock screen, so the launcher home and recents — which read
WALLPAPER_SYSTEM through the wallpaper manager — show the one managed Oniro
wallpaper instead of the stock blue default. Pairs with the existing
0001-replace-wallpaperlockdefault patch.

Change-Id: Ia9e32b72fcf8029277c7b564ddda628ac85bebde
Signed-off-by: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 frameworks/native/data/wallpaperdefault.jpeg | Bin 63543 -> 90448 bytes
 1 file changed, 0 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/frameworks/native/data/wallpaperdefault.jpeg b/frameworks/native/data/wallpaperdefault.jpeg
